 presupposti fondamentali dell’analisi, quale si è praticata per lo più da studiosi germanofoni nel sec. XIX e nella prima metà del XX.  aThrough a detailed philological analysis, Carlo Lucarini distinguishes the poets who have composed the Iliad and the Odyssey, which are, in fact, patchworks put together by two Bearbeiter at the end of VII c. BC. By doing so, he sheds new light on the vexata quaestio of the composition of both poems, opening the way for further research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aEpic poetry. 0aHomer. 0aIliad. 0aIlias. 0aOdyssee. 0aanalysis. 4aHomer. 4aIlias. 4aOdyssee. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aHomer.  aIliad.  aanalysis.  aepic poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106501360 cprintz978311065004440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311065296340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110652963423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110652963.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019